reviewText:
Well if you didn't like the second Speed but want to own it for the collection this is for you. Its a two disc box set, its just one case but the cover art is awesome.

Speed: is the original Blu-ray that came out a while back but the picture and sound quality are excellent. I would give it a 10/10 for content and 10/10 for picture and sound.

Speed 2: is a very well planed Blu-ray the sound a picture quality are great. Part 2 however does fall short on content 7/10, but sound and picture its a 10/10.

So two thumbs up TWENTYTH CENTRY FOX.

I have seen  both Speed & Speed 2: Cruise Control and I really enjoyed both of them. Matter of fact, I have both of them on DVD. I wanted to get them on Blu-Ray for a two reasons: first I wanted to see the behind the scenes look at both Speed 1 & 2 because the DVDs I own have nothing but the trailers. Second,  I wanted to see what the picture quality would look like on Blu-Ray because I've never own a Blu-Ray before. The good news I have already order it and it came .  my only concerns is I hope I won't have any problems with this in the future.  Speed I give 5 stars and Speed 2: Cruise Control I give 4 stars. Totally recommend getting this bluray two-pack if you are a big fan of speed 1 & 2 !

I watched Speed a million times when it first came out... you know, back on VHS (anyone remember what that is?)!  I don't know why it took me so long to purchase the move on DVD, but was glad to find the set.  I still like Speed and the sequel was pretty good... but either the technology is still old or the quality of the Blu-ray that I got just happened to be bad.  It skipped a lot and froze at one point... luckily recovering a little while later.  I realize people don't like getting reviews on here about whether a movie works or not, but it affects the experience (in my opinion) so I have it in here.  Overall, worth it as long as you can get it to work!  I was entertained all over again watching these movies!  (I also forgot how gross Speed was at times! Haha)
